      • setSamplingRate

        public static void setSamplingRate​(MentalabConstants.SamplingRate samplingRate)
                            throws CommandFailedException,
                                   NoBluetoothException,
                                   InvalidCommandException,
                                   java.io.IOException
        Sets sampling rate of the device

        Sampling rate only applies to ExG data. Orientation and Environment data are always sampled at 20Hz. Currently available sampling rates are 250,500 and 1000 Hz. Default is 250Hz.

        Parameters:
        samplingRate - enumerator to choose sampling rate
        Throws:
        CommandFailedException - when sampling rate change fails
        NoBluetoothException
        InvalidCommandException
        java.io.IOException

      • setEnabled

        public static void setEnabled​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Boolean> switches)
                       throws CommandFailedException,
                              NoConnectionException,
                              NoBluetoothException,
                              InvalidCommandException,
                              java.io.IOException
        Enables or disables data collection per module or channel. Only support enabling/disabling one module in one call. Mixing enable and disable switch will lead to erroneous result

        By default data from all modules is collected. Disable modules you do not need to save bandwidth and power. Calling setEnabled with a partial map is supported. Trying to enable a channel that the device does not have results in a CommandFailedException thrown. When a CommandFailedException is received from this method, none or only some of the switches may have been set.

        Parameters:
        switches - Map of modules to on (true) or off (false) state accelerometer, magnetometer, gyroscope, environment, channel0 ..channel7
        Throws:
        CommandFailedException
        NoConnectionException
        NoBluetoothException
        InvalidCommandException
        java.io.IOException
